% Session 1, Exercise 6: Creating function files

% This function file is created as part of exercise 6.  The function here
% tests whether the input value ("value_to_test") is odd or even.  The
% function returns the value stored locally as "state", which is either
% "true" if the input value is odd, or "false) if the
% value is even.

function state = isodd(value_to_test)
if rem(value_to_test,2) == 1
    state = logical(1);
else
   state = logical(0); 
end
